<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-03-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="826" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d826">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.48 Earthquake of 1931/15:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the President of Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moncada</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-31">March 31, 1931</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I am profoundly distressed by the reports of the overwhelming disaster
                            which has befallen Nicaragua. Please be assured of my heartfelt
                            sympathy.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Henry L. Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>